            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--epitaph of Kalikrates and? Mang attempts a full restoration, but Dubois, BE 1997 thinks it tenuous! Cf. Curbera's re-ed. The name Nounphion is v. rare. This not a true funerary inscr., but rather records the acquisition of plot of land for the grave. Located by AMM 31.03.15.-->
                    <!-- J.WC. Kamar.15b p.01(2)-02(2): «Seems to be a legal document, on the acquisition of the 2 parents of an area for the tomb (χωρη!) of their son Mounphin (should read Monphin) and themselves. The parents 
                    are Kallik. and Aisa, K. be called bastard of Kallippos, viz. had Sikel mother? [...] till we get a good copy, my reading very doubtful». --></p>
            </div>
